{
  "text": "Neurological deficits were evaluated by an observer (G.-S.C.) blinded to the age and treatment of each mouse at 6 hours and 1, 2, and 3 days after blood injection. Tests included a postural reflex test, which examines upper-body posture while the animal is suspended by the tail, and a forelimb placing test, which examines sensorimotor integration in the forelimb to visual, tactile, and proprioceptive stimuli. Neurological function was graded on a scale of 0 to 12 (normal score\u03ed0, maximal score\u03ed12) as described previously. [CITATION_1] ",
